Hi @XxDaLeBeAsTxX, I am sorry to say but your computer may be too old to play the 1.1 update, the graphics version supported by your hardware is no longer supported by KSP.

This is just too old, and was released in 2007.

Quote

Renderer: Intel(R) G33/G31 Express Chipset Family

This graphics chip only supports shader model 2.0, but KSP needs shader model 3.0 to work properly.

You can try enabling the unsupported legacy shaders in the settings.cfg file in the KSP folder, but it is not guaranteed to work.

You could also try setting all graphics to their minimum in the launcher, by clicking the gear icon.

If these do not help then I am afraid you may have to play the previous version until you are able to upgrade.

I wish I had better news for you, but maybe other forum members have had luck getting KSP 1.1 to work on this graphics chip, and will be able to offer some advice.
